    <string name="about_app_description">ElecBill Calculator is an Android application that assists Malaysians to determine their monthly bills based on the TNB tiered block rate scheme. Just input the number of units consumed and select the desired rebate, and the application will instantly tell you what your charges and total costs are.</string>
    <string name="about_how_to_use_title">How to Use</string>
    <string name="about_how_to_use">1. Select the billing month from the dropdown.\n2. Enter the number of electricity units used (1–1000 kWh) in the input field.\n3. Choose the rebate percentage (0%–5%) using the slider.\n4. Tap CALCULATE to see the total charges and final cost.\n5. Tap SAVE TO DATABASE to store the record.\n6. Tap VIEW HISTORY to browse all saved records.\n7. In the History screen, tap any entry to view its full details, or to edit/delete it.</string>
    <string name="about_tariff_title">TNB Domestic Tariff (Peninsular Malaysia)</string>
    <string name="about_tariff">Block 1 (1–200 kWh): 21.8 sen/kWh\nBlock 2 (201–300 kWh): 33.4 sen/kWh\nBlock 3 (301–600 kWh): 51.6 sen/kWh\nBlock 4 (601–1000 kWh): 54.6 sen/kWh</string>

    <!-- Instruction banner on main screen -->
    <string name="instruction_banner">Select a month, enter units (1–1000 kWh), choose rebate, then tap Calculate.</string>
